<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
This species was moved from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Diaphorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diaphorus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Diaphorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysotus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Chrysotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.9607" author="Becker, T" journalOrPublisher="Kansas University Science Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" refId="B4" refString="Becker, T, 1922. Dipterologische Studien, Dolichopodidae. B. Nearktische und Neotropische Region. Abhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wein (1921) 13(1): 1-394. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.9607" title="Dipterologische Studien, Dolichopodidae. B. Nearktische und Neotropische Region. Abhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wein (1921) 13 (1): 1 - 394." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.9607" year="1922">Becker (1922</bibRefCitation>
, page 170), an act that has gone largely unnoticed. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Becker’s">Becker's</normalizedToken>
move was correct because this species does not fit in the current definition of the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Diaphorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Diaphorus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Diaphorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Remarks for 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. interfrons" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="interfrons">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">C. interfrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov.). In particular it lacks setae on the upper proepisternum, black calypteral setae, a completely bare tergite 6, and four to eight long strong setae on sternite 8. The species fits in the broadly defined 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1824" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chrysotus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Chrysotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
following 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1206/0003-0090(2004)283&lt;0001:COTDDO&gt;2.0.CO;2" author="Pollet, MA" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 114" refId="B57" refString="Pollet, MA, Brooks, SE, Cumming, JM, 2004. Catalog of the Dolichopodidae (Diptera) of America north of Mexico. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 283: 1 - 114, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1206/0003-0090(2004)283&lt;0001:COTDDO&gt;2.0.CO;2" title="Catalog of the Dolichopodidae (Diptera) of America north of Mexico." url="https://doi.org/10.1206/0003-0090(2004)283&lt;0001:COTDDO&gt;2.0.CO;2" volume="283" year="2004">Pollet et al. (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, which is likely paraphyletic and might need subdivision as diaphorine phylogeny is elucidated (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2520.1.2" author="Capellari, RS" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="49 - 65" refId="B20" refString="Capellari, RS, Amorim, DS, 2010. Re-description and new combination of five New World species of Chrysotus Meigen, with comments on the Neotropical genus Lyroneurus Loew (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Zootaxa 2520: 49 - 65, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2520.1.2" title="Re-description and new combination of five New World species of Chrysotus Meigen, with comments on the Neotropical genus Lyroneurus Loew (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2520.1.2" volume="2520" year="2010">Capellari and Amorim 2010</bibRefCitation>
). This necessitates a new replacement name for the Nearctic 
<taxonomicName genus="Chysotus" lsidName="Chysotus parvulus" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="parvulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Chysotus parvulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Van Duzee, 1924, as:
</paragraph>
